HEADWORD: Hammer lock
<hw>Hammer lock</hw>. <fld>(Wrestling)</fld> <def>A hold in which an arm
of one contestant is held twisted and bent behind his back by his
opponent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

